      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STORM SISTER (8) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by a nose at Murray Bridge Straight in a handy 17.15 beating Shiny Pistol. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from six attempts. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. PRETTY ESMAY (4) continues to race well but is struggling to break through, placing at her last four runs. Last time finished 2nd in a Grade 6 on July 3 over 530m at this track behind Adhana Henry beaten 3 lengths (31.04). Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Deserves a win and gets her chance. GETTING CHEEKY (7) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 4 lengths at Murray Bridge Straight in a handy 17.43 beating Elegant Cindy. Has good speed and will be prominent from out wide. One of the prime contenders. RIVERSIDE BEAST (1) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.",
